Sentencas: Little is known about the structures and chemistry of perovskites, occurring from the surface to the bulk, at high temperatures and ambient oxygen pressures.
Titulo: Surface Strontium Segregation of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Cathodes Proved by In Situ Depth-Resolved X-ray Absorption Spectroscopy

Sentencas: Changes in the composition and electronic structure of (001)-oriented La0.8Sr0.2CoO3-delta (LSC) films were investigated by using in situ depth-resolved X-ray adsorption (XAS) under practical operating conditions of solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Surface Strontium Segregation of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Cathodes Proved by In Situ Depth-Resolved X-ray Absorption Spectroscopy

Sentencas: Depth-resolved XAS spectra of LSC films, with a depth resolution of similar to 2 nm, revealed that the surface regions of similar to 10 nm were considerably different from the film bulk.
Titulo: Surface Strontium Segregation of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Cathodes Proved by In Situ Depth-Resolved X-ray Absorption Spectroscopy

Sentencas: The surface regions were enriched in strontium, which can play an important role in governing the oxygen exchange kinetics at the surface.
Titulo: Surface Strontium Segregation of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Cathodes Proved by In Situ Depth-Resolved X-ray Absorption Spectroscopy
